R19-1-210.
Tax requirements No licensed wholesaler or retailer shall have in his possession or sell any spirituous liquors on which the state luxury taxes have not been accounted for as provided by law and upon which all federal taxes imposed by law have not been paid.
Historical Note Former Rule 10; Former Section R4-15-29 renumbered as Section R4-15-210 without change effective October 8, 1982 (Supp. 82-5).
