Amended effective September 14, 1990, under an exemption from the Administrative Procedure Act pursuant to Laws 1989, Ch. 234, Ã¯Â¿Â½ 22; filed March 31, 1999 R19-1-215.
Credit Law Exception Wholesalers, distillers, brewers, and vintners licensed by this Department making sales of spirituous liquor to other licensed wholesalers, distillers, brewers and vintners shall be exempt from the credit restriction of A.R.S. Ã¯Â¿Â½ 4-242.
The intention of this rule is to permit such licensees the same privileges as out-of-state licensees and to prevent discrimination against Arizona licensees in accordance with the established trade customs in this state.
