R19-1-216.
Suspension, Adherence to Rules of During the suspension of a license, the licensee shall not allow, permit, or suffer the sale, service, delivery, or consumption of any spirituous liquor on or about the licensed premises, nor order or receive delivery of any spirituous liquor.
The notice of suspension shall be prominently displayed on the premises at all times during the period of suspension.
Historical Note Former Rule 16; Former Section R4-15-35 renumbered as Section R4-15-216 without change effective October 8, 1982 (Supp. 82-5).
R19-1-216 recodified from R4-15216 (Supp. 95-1).
