R19-1-222.
Records, Keeping of All licensees shall keep for a period of not less than 2 years all invoices, records, bills and other papers and documents relating to the purchase, sale and delivery of alcoholic beverages.
Such records and papers shall be kept in such conditions of storage as to be easily accessible to the Director or any peace officer designated by the Director for examination or audit.
