R19-1-229.
Liquors other than authorized by license No licensee, either through himself or through an agent, shall sell, solicit, or receive an order, keep or expose for sale, deliver for value, peddle, keep with intent to sell or traffic in or have for any purposes upon his licensed premises any spirituous liquors other than those set forth in his license.
