R19-1-231.
Hotel/Motel/Restaurant Requirements A Hotel/Motel licensee and a Restaurant licensee must maintain complete restaurant services as defined under A.R.S. Ã¯Â¿Â½Ã¯Â¿Â½ 4-205.01, and 4-205.02, continually during the hours of selling and serving spirituous liquors.
Restaurant services, as defined under these statutes, is compulsory to 10 p.m. daily if any spirituous liquors are to be sold and served to the legal hours.
A requested meal which is refused during these hours will constitute sufficient evidence that the licensed business has ceased to operate as a bona fide restaurant.
